<keyLead id="DD2E9599FF9DFF9CBDAABFFB11E58D92" box="[151,1437,665,686]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">
5. Posterior parapods each with 9–11 claws; anal tubules 71–117 µm long, with 1–2 constrictions... 
<taxonomicName id="A1DF4D2FFF9DFF9CB948BFFB11368D92" authority="(Strenzke)" baseAuthorityName="Strenzke" box="[1141,1358,665,686]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Hydrosmittia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis id="54ABEABEFF9DFF9CB948BFFB10908D92" box="[1141,1256,665,686]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">H. montana</emphasis>
(Strenzke)
</taxonomicName>
(p. 118)
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="666036ACFF9DFF9CBDAABFD511E58DF0" blockId="106.[151,1437,249,716]" box="[151,1437,695,716]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">
<keyLead id="DD2E9599FF9DFF9CBDAABFD511E58DF0" box="[151,1437,695,716]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">
